name: Flour
description: It is a powder made by grinding raw grains, roots, beans, nuts, or seeds.

name: Eggs
description: They are laid by female animals of many different species, including birds, reptiles, amphibians, a few mammals, and fish, and many of these have been eaten by humans for thousands of years.

name: Sugar
description: It is the generic name for sweet-tasting, soluble carbohydrates, many of which are used in food.

name: Milk
description: It is a nutrient-rich liquid food produced by the mammary glands of mammals.

name: Olive oil
description: is a liquid fat obtained from olives, a traditional tree crop of the Mediterranean Basin, produced by pressing whole olives and extracting the oil.

name: Spice
description: It is a seed, fruit, root, bark, or other plant substance primarily used for flavoring or coloring food.

name: Butter
description: It is a dairy product made from the fat and protein components of churned cream.

name: Salt
description: It is a mineral composed primarily of sodium chloride (NaCl).

name: Chicken
description: It is a domesticated junglefowl species.

name: Rice
description: It is the seed of the grass species Oryza sativa (Asian rice) or less commonly Oryza glaberrima (African rice).

name: Pork
description: It is the culinary name for the meat of the domestic pig.

name: Beef
description: It is the culinary name for meat from cattle.

name: Cheese
description: It is a dairy product produced in wide ranges of flavors, textures, and forms by coagulation of the milk protein casein.

name: Garlic
description: It is a species of bulbous flowering plant in the genus Allium.

name: Onion
description: It is a vegetable that is the most widely cultivated species of the genus Allium.

name: Corn
description: It is a cereal grain first domesticated by indigenous peoples in southern Mexico about 10,000 years ago.
